'''Yossi Brodny''' ({{lang-he-n|יוסי ברודני}}; born 15 January 1971) is an [[Israel]]i politician and current mayor of the Israeli city of [[Giv'at Shmuel]] since 2008.

==Biography==
Brodny was born in [[Hadera]]. He served in [[Israel Defense Forces]] (IDF) between 1989 until 1996 in the [[Paratroopers Brigade]].

===Political career===

Since 2003 until 2008 Brodny served as member of [[Giv'at Shmuel]] council. In 2008 was elected mayor of Giv'at Shmuel and has served in his position. In 2009 he joined the [[Likud]] party. In October 2013 he was elected mayor again, this time without competing.

